article.headline: Cato has double-double as Central Arkansas takes down North Florida 79-77
article.description: — Elias Cato had 14 points and 10 rebounds in Central Arkansas' 79-77 win over North Florida on Saturday night.
article.linkText: Cato has double-double as Central Arkansas takes down North Florida 79-77
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. -- — Elias Cato had 14 points and 10 rebounds in Central Arkansas' 79-77 win over North Florida on Saturday night. Masai Olowokere also scored 14 points for Central Arkansas (9-18, 5-6 Atlantic Sun Conference). He was 5 of 9 shooting and 3 of 3 from the free throw line. Tucker Anderson had 12 points and was 5 of 7 shooting (2 for 3 from 3-point range). The Bears held on to the lead over the final six minutes. Chaz Lanier led the way for the Ospreys (13-13, 6-5) with 21 points and eight rebounds. Nate Lliteras added 16 points and two steals for North Florida. Oscar Berry also had 13 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
